<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,503,1544,1571]" box="[151,503,1544,1571]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,503,1544,1571]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,503,1544,1571]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li &amp; Sattler" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[151,418,1545,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Mesophleps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tephrastis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,418,1545,1571]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Mesophleps tephrastis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1609,2029]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
Labial palpus recurved, segment 2 with large, sub-triangular, anteriorly-directed tuft, 3 long, recurved. Fore wing ochreous yellow, fuscous or grey, with or without indistinct markings. Pregenital abdomen with transverse bands of microtrichia on anterior margins of TIV–VII (
<figureCitation box="[666,750,1681,1705]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[198,1404,207,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-78@13.[179,1423,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. Abdomens of Mesophleps spp. 17. M. safranella (Legrand), ♀, slide no. 30970; 18. M. epiochra (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 15833; 19. M. geodes (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 30939; 20. M. geodes (Meyrick), ♀, slide no. 30937; 21. M. catericta (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 30972; 22. M. tephrastis (Meyrick), ♀, slide no. 30947." pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); segments VIII (
<specimenCount box="[946,965,1681,1700]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
) and VII (
<specimenCount box="[1083,1102,1681,1700]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
) usually unremarkable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1609,2029]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,311,1717,1742]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Genitalia</emphasis>
<specimenCount box="[319,338,1716,1735]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation box="[353,485,1717,1741]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–88" captionStartId="73.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[204,1386,194,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-71@73.[181,1405,181,1930]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 83–88. Male genitalia of Mesophleps spp., genus? and Sarotorna. 83. M. catericta (Meyrick), slide no. 30972; 84. M. tetrachroa (Lower), slide no. 30945; 85. M. tephrastis (Meyrick), slide no. 30948; 86. M. chloranthes (Lower), slide no. 30968; 87.? mesophracta (Turner), slide no. 30958; 88. Sarotorna mesoleuca (Lower), slide no. 11620, ANIC." pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Figs 84–86</figureCitation>
). Uncus variable, long, tapered or sub-rectangular; gnathos arms connate or fused to one; tegumen unremarkable, sometimes long, anterior margin concave, pedunculi simple, curved; valva simple; vinculum distally broad, posterior margin more strongly sclerotized medially, notched or extended to pair of bumps or processes; phallus typical of genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1609,2029]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,311,1861,1886]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Genitalia</emphasis>
<specimenCount box="[320,339,1860,1879]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation box="[354,442,1861,1885]" captionStart="FIGURES 9, 10" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1974,1997]" captionTargetBox="[226,1373,354,1942]" captionTargetId="figure-106@11.[191,1396,332,1962]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 9, 10. Female genitalia of Mesophleps spp. 9. M. parvella sp. nov. paratype, slide no. 30951; 10. M. tetrachroa (Lower), slide no. 30946." pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[455,554,1861,1885]" captionStart="FIGURES 112–118" captionStartId="78.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[255,1360,190,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-77@78.[181,1405,177,1905]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURES 112–118. Female genitalia of Mesophleps spp. and Sarotorna sp. 112. M. tephrastis (Meyrick), slide no. 30947; 113. M. trichombra (Lower), slide no. 30950; 114. M. mylicotis (Meyrick), slide no. 30949; 115. M. macrosemus (Lower), slide no. 30938; 116. M. chloranthes (Lower), slide no. 30942; 117. M. argonota (Lower), slide no. 30986; 118. Sarotorna mesoleuca (Lower), slide no. 11613, ANIC." pageId="49" pageNumber="50">112–117</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[566,668,1861,1885]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–150" captionStartId="81.[151,264,1575,1598]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1530]" captionTargetId="figure-85@81.[151,1436,193,1554]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="FIGURES 143–150. Female segment VIII of Mesophleps spp. and Sarotorna sp. 143. M. tephrastis (Meyrick), slide no. 30947; 144. M. tetrachroa (Lower), slide no. 30946; 145. M. trichombra (Lower), slide no. 30950; 146. M. mylicotis (Meyrick), slide no. 30949; 147. M. macrosemus (Lower), slide no. 30938; 148. M. chloranthes (Lower), slide no. 30942; 149. M. argonota (Lower), slide no. 30986; 150. Sarotorna mesoleuca (Lower), slide no. 11613, ANIC." pageId="49" pageNumber="50">143–149</figureCitation>
). Papillae anales specialized, long, narrow, well sclerotized, moderately set with relatively short sensory setae; apophyses posteriores and anteriores long; antrum variable, sometimes with long, narrow sclerotization; ductus bursae narrow, at most length of apophyses anteriores, corpus bursae large, oval to elongate, ductus seminalis from cervix bursae near entrance of ductus bursae, surface of cervix bursae set with microtrichia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,316,152,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
Most of the fifteen Australian species placed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick, 1904" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1904" box="[862,1156,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Xerometra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[862,981,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Xerometra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick, E." box="[988,1156,151,175]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="255 - 441" refId="ref53748" refString="Meyrick, E. (1904) Descriptions of Australian Microlepidoptera. XVIII. Gelechiadae. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales, 29, 255 - 441." type="journal article" year="1904">Meyrick, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, in the Australian checklist (
<bibRefCitation author="Edwards, E. D." box="[201,424,188,212]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref52109" refString="Edwards, E. D. (1996) See Nielsen, E. S., Edwards, E. D. &amp; Rangsi, V. 1996." type="journal volume" year="1996">Edwards 1996: 108</bibRefCitation>
) are closely related and constitute a distinct species-group within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1825" box="[1178,1312,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Mesophleps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1178,1312,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Mesophleps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the type-species 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick, 1904" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1904" box="[338,628,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Xerometra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocina">
<emphasis box="[338,454,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">X. crocina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick, E." box="[460,628,223,247]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="255 - 441" refId="ref53748" refString="Meyrick, E. (1904) Descriptions of Australian Microlepidoptera. XVIII. Gelechiadae. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales, 29, 255 - 441." type="journal article" year="1904">Meyrick, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is not part of this group but is referable to the 
<taxonomicName box="[1154,1301,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Brachyacma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palpigera">
<emphasis box="[1154,1301,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">M. palpigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group. One species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Turner 1919)" authorityName="Li &amp; Sattler" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Turner" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[249,599,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Nothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesophracta">
<emphasis box="[249,428,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">X. mesophracta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Turner, A. J." box="[444,591,260,284]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="108 - 172" refId="ref55069" refString="Turner, A. J. (1919) The Australian Gelechianae (Lepidoptera). Proceedings of the Royal Society of Qeensland, 31, 108 - 172." type="journal article" year="1919">Turner 1919</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, has to be removed to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pitkin" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[869,1006,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Gelechiidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1926" box="[1020,1189,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Anomologinae">Anomologinae</taxonomicName>
, although no suitable genus can currently be suggested. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Turner 1919)" authorityName="Li &amp; Sattler" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Turner" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[550,869,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Pycnobathra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acromelas">
<emphasis box="[550,700,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">X. acromelas</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Turner, A. J." box="[717,861,295,319]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="108 - 172" refId="ref55069" refString="Turner, A. J. (1919) The Australian Gelechianae (Lepidoptera). Proceedings of the Royal Society of Qeensland, 31, 108 - 172." type="journal article" year="1919">Turner 1919</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is here transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lower, 1901" authorityName="Lower" authorityYear="1901" box="[1129,1431,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Pycnobathra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1129,1274,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Pycnobathra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lower, O. B." box="[1284,1431,295,319]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="63 - 98" refId="ref53566" refString="Lower, O. B. (1901) Descriptions of new genera and species of Australian Lepidoptera. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Australia, 25, 63 - 98." type="journal article" year="1901">Lower, 1901</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, whilst 
<taxonomicName authority="Lower, 1901" authorityName="Lower" authorityYear="1901" box="[226,612,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Plutellidae" genus="Ypsolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argonota">
<emphasis box="[226,461,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Ypsolophus argonota</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lower, O. B." box="[468,612,332,356]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="63 - 98" refId="ref53566" refString="Lower, O. B. (1901) Descriptions of new genera and species of Australian Lepidoptera. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Australia, 25, 63 - 98." type="journal article" year="1901">Lower, 1901</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is transferred from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lower" authorityYear="1901" box="[839,984,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Pycnobathra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[839,984,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Pycnobathra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the Australian list incorrectly placed as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zeller, 1839" authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1839" box="[415,736,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[415,592,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Megacraspedus</emphasis>
Zeller, 1839
</taxonomicName>
) to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1825" box="[780,914,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Mesophleps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[780,914,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Mesophleps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1839" box="[1051,1228,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1051,1228,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Megacraspedus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the Palaearctic Region and is not represented in the Australian fauna. The generic position of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick, 1886" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calamogonus">
<emphasis box="[1179,1366,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">M. calamogonus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick, E." pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="189 - 296" refId="ref53719" refString="Meyrick, E. (1886) Descriptions of Lepidoptera from the South Pacific. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1886, 189 - 296." type="journal article" year="1886">Meyrick, 1886</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[340,490,439,463]" name="New Zealand" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick, 1909" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1909" box="[544,825,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serica">
<emphasis box="[544,567,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[582,650,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">serica</emphasis>
Meyrick, 1909
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[897,1041,439,463]" name="South Africa" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">South Africa</collectingCountry>
is uncertain, but neither belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1839" box="[151,328,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,328,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Megacraspedus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
